A robber who stole £650 from a betting shop was caught by police - after they recognised his giant chin on CCTV.

Ricky Loft, from Greenhithe, Kent, stormed into a William Hill bookies armed with an 'imitation gun', which was wrapped in a black bin liner.

The 32-year-old thug pointed the weapon at staff and ordered a worker to fill a bag with cash.

