Loft, who was wearing a hood covering the top half of his face, then escaped from the shop on Whitstable high street.

Staff from the betting shop reported the raid, which took place on November 21 last year, but could only describe the bottom half of the robber's face.

But the breakthrough came when police examined CCTV footage from the betting shop - and spotted the raider had a 'prominent chin'.

A mugshot of Loft, who was known to police before that incident, was already on police file.

When police compared the mugshot to the CCTV stills, they noticed both men had a jutting chin - and that it must be the same man.

